The paper focuses on improving sentence representations by jointly training them with associated image features, which is a common theme in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a self-attention mechanism to deepen the grounding effect, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates the performance of the proposed method on transfer tasks, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR).
